aa(lp208
VAnd by the way, one of the things that really bothers me
p209
aVabout some of the rhetoric against feminists and others
p210
aVwho have built the battered women's and rape crisis movements around the world
p211
aVis that somehow, like I said, that they're anti-male.
p212
aVWhat about all the boys who are profoundly affected in a negative way
p213
aVby what some adult man is doing against their mother, themselves, their sisters?
p214
aVWhat about all those boys?
p215
aVWhat about all the young men and boys
p216
aVwho have been traumatized by adult men's violence?
p217
aVYou know what?
p218
aVThe same system that produces men who abuse women,
p219
aVproduces men who abuse other men.
p220
aVAnd if we want to talk about male victims, let's talk about male victims.
p221
aVMost male victims of violence are the victims of other men's violence.
p222
aVSo that's something that both women and men have in common.
p223
aVWe are both victims of men's violence.
p224
aVSo we have it in our direct self-interest,
p225
aVnot to mention the fact that most men that I know
p226
aVhave women and girls that we care deeply about,
p227
aVin our families and our friendship circles and every other way.
